#: maxframe.tensor.reduction.nanmean.nanmean of
msgid "返回"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.reduction.nanmean.nanmean:34 of
msgid ""
"**m** -- If `out=None`, returns a new array containing the mean values, "
"otherwise a reference to the output array is returned. Nan is returned "
"for slices that contain only NaNs."
msgstr ""
"**m** -- 如果 `out=None`，则返回一个包含平均值的新数组，否则返回对输出"
"数组的引用。对于只包含 NaN 的切片，返回 NaN。"

#: maxframe.tensor.reduction.nanmean.nanmean of
msgid "返回类型"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.reduction.nanmean.nanmean:41 of
msgid ":py:obj:`average`"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.reduction.nanmean.nanmean:42 of
msgid "Weighted average"
msgstr "加权平均值"

#: maxframe.tensor.reduction.nanmean.nanmean:44 of
msgid ":py:obj:`mean`"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.reduction.nanmean.nanmean:45 of
msgid "Arithmetic mean taken while not ignoring NaNs"
msgstr "计算算术平均值时不忽略 NaN"

#: maxframe.tensor.reduction.nanmean.nanmean:47 of
msgid ":py:obj:`var`, :py:obj:`nanvar`"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.reduction.nanmean.nanmean:50 of
msgid "备注"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.reduction.nanmean.nanmean:51 of
msgid ""
"The arithmetic mean is the sum of the non-NaN elements along the axis "
"divided by the number of non-NaN elements."
msgstr "算术平均值是沿轴的非 NaN 元素之和除以非 NaN 元素的数量。"

#: maxframe.tensor.reduction.nanmean.nanmean:54 of
msgid ""
"Note that for floating-point input, the mean is computed using the same "
"precision the input has.  Depending on the input data, this can cause the"
" results to be inaccurate, especially for `float32`.  Specifying a "
"higher-precision accumulator using the `dtype` keyword can alleviate this"
" issue."
msgstr ""
"注意，对于浮点数输入，平均值是使用与输入相同的精度计算的。根据输入数据的"
"不同，这可能导致结果不准确，特别是对于 `float32`。使用 `dtype` 关键字指定"
"更高精度的累加器可以缓解此问题。"

